同时，不同领域的医生或医学专家对于医生协助自杀的态度也不一致。经过对全英姑息治疗委员会（{{lang|en|National Council for Palliative Care}}）、{{Link-en|耆英协进会|Age Concern}}、协助临终关怀组织（{{lang|en|Help the Hospices}}）、{{Link-en|麦克米伦癌症支持组织|Macmillan Cancer Support}}、{{Link-en|英国运动神经元病协会|Motor Neurone Disease Association}}、{{Link-en|大不列颠多发性硬化症学会|Multiple Sclerosis Society of Great Britain}}和{{Link-en|苏莱德 (慈善组织)|Sue Ryder (charity)|苏莱德关怀机构}}等组织的3733名医学专家的调查，结果发现在[[姑息治疗|姑息治疗]]和{{Link-en|老年关怀|Elderly care}}领域的医师对于医生协助自杀的反对意见最大，超过90%的姑息治疗医师反对修改法律。<ref name="cohen" />

[[格拉斯哥大学|格拉斯哥大学]]医学法律与伦理研究所在1997年的一项调查显示，约有72%的[[药剂师|药剂师]]和56%的[[麻醉师|麻醉师]]是支持医生协助自杀的。药剂师像[[全科医师|全科医师]]那样认同一个观点，即“如果患者决定结束自己的生命，那么法律应该允许医师去提供帮助”。<ref>McLean, Sheila, and Alison Britton. Sometimes a small victory. Institute of Law and Ethics, University of Glasgow, 1996.</ref> [[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]]在2017年1月发布的一份报告显示，由于市政当局允许医师拒绝在美国境内协助自杀，这使得原本因为协助自杀合法化而获得相应资格的病患找不到合适的协助者。<ref>{{cite web |author1=JoNel Aleccia |title=Legalizing Aid In Dying Doesn't Mean Patients Have Access To It |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2017/01/25/511456109/legalizing-aid-in-dying-doesnt-mean-patients-have-access-to-it |publisher=[[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]] |accessdate=2019-03-14 |archive-date=2019-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222214623/https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2017/01/25/511456109/legalizing-aid-in-dying-doesnt-mean-patients-have-access-to-it |dead-url=no }}</ref>

英国的一项民意调查显示，54%的[[全科医师|全科医师]]对引入协助自杀法律持支持或中立态度。<ref>{{cite web |title=PUBLIC OPINION |url=https://www.dignityindying.org.uk/assisted-dying/public-opinion/ |publisher=Dignity in Dying |accessdate=2019-03-14 |archive-date=2019-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514142940/https://www.dignityindying.org.uk/assisted-dying/public-opinion/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>而《[[英国医学期刊|英国医学期刊]]》发表的一项针对{{Link-en|Doctors.net.uk|Doctors.net.uk}}用户的类似调查显示，55%的医生将支持协助自杀立法。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Paul Gallagher |title=Assisted dying case ‘stronger than ever’ with majority of doctors now in support |url=https://inews.co.uk/news/health/assisted-dying-debate-bmj-doctors-majority-support/ |publisher=iNews.co.uk |accessdate=2019-03-14 |archive-date=2019-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190515040235/https://inews.co.uk/news/health/assisted-dying-debate-bmj-doctors-majority-support/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>但是代表英国医生的[[英国医学会|英国医学会]]则反对这样的立法。<ref>{{cite web |title=Physician-assisted dying |url=https://www.bma.org.uk/advice/employment/ethics/ethics-a-to-z/physician-assisted-dying |publisher=[[英国医学会|英国医学会]] |accessdate=2019-03-14 |archive-date=2019-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514040428/https://www.bma.org.uk/advice/employment/ethics/ethics-a-to-z/physician-assisted-dying |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2000年一项针对[[北爱尔兰|北爱尔兰地区]]全科医师的匿名、保密邮件调查显示，在回应调查的70%人员是反对医生协助自杀和自愿主动安乐死。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Kieran J McGlade |author2=L Slaney |author3=B P Bunting |author4=Anthony Gallagher |title=Voluntary euthanasia in Northern Ireland: General practitioners' beliefs, experiences, and actions |journal=British Journal of General Practice |date=2000-10 |volume=50 |issue=459 |pages=794-7 |pmid=11127168 |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/12202069_Voluntary_euthanasia_in_Northern_Ireland_General_practitioners'_beliefs_experiences_and_actions |accessdate=2019-03-14 |archive-date=2019-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222054317/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/12202069_Voluntary_euthanasia_in_Northern_Ireland_General_practitioners'_beliefs_experiences_and_actions |dead-url=no }}</ref>

